  "solution": {
    "answer": "$H_0(T^2) \\cong \\mathbb{Z},\\quad H_1(T^2) \\cong \\mathbb{Z}^2,\\quad H_2(T^2) \\cong \\mathbb{Z},\\quad H_n = 0 \\text{ for } n \\geq 3.$",
    "steps": [
      "CW structure: one 0-cell $v$, two 1-cells $a, b$, one 2-cell $e$. Attaching word: $aba^{-1}b^{-1}$.",
      "Chain groups: $C_2 = \\mathbb{Z}\\langle e\\rangle$, $C_1 = \\mathbb{Z}\\langle a\\rangle \\oplus \\mathbb{Z}\\langle b\\rangle$, $C_0 = \\mathbb{Z}\\langle v\\rangle$.",
      "$d_1(a) = v - v = 0$, $d_1(b) = v - v = 0$. So $d_1 = 0$.",
      "$d_2(e)$: the 2-cell boundary traverses $a$ once forward and once backward (net $0$), and $b$ once forward and once backward (net $0$). Thus $d_2 = 0$.",
      "$H_2 = \\ker(d_2)/\\operatorname{im}(d_3) = \\mathbb{Z}/0 = \\mathbb{Z}$.",
      "$H_1 = \\ker(d_1)/\\operatorname{im}(d_2) = \\mathbb{Z}^2/0 = \\mathbb{Z}^2$, generated by $[a]$ and $[b]$.",
      "$H_0 = \\mathbb{Z}$. All higher groups vanish."
    ]
  },
